17. primis: i.e. L. Julius Caesar and P. Licinius Crassus, who as censors of 89 13.c. were the first to enroll those who had gained citizenship by the lex Plautia—Papiria.

18. census . . . cive: i.e. the census does not establish the right of citizenship, but merely proves that the person who is re· turned in the census has at the time the status of a citizen.
